Somatic cognition → literally “thinking with the body.” Used in embodied mind theory.
Plexus → Latin for “braid” or “network,” used in anatomy for interwoven nerve networks.
Syneidesis (Greek: συνείδησις = “knowing together”) → used in philosophy/theology for a collective conscience.
Polycephaly (Greek: “many-headedness”) → normally for myths/monsters, but apt.

